A BRAVE student has revealed her <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anorexia_nervosa" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anorexia_nervosa" target="_blank">anorexia</a> hell after her weight plummeted to just 4st 11lb as she lived on three teaspoons of asparagus a dayTroubled Lydia Davies was surviving on 13 <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Calorie" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Calorie" target="_blank">calories</a> a day and looked like a living skeletonAfter she was <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diagnosis" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diagnosis" target="_blank">diagnosed</a> with <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anorexia_nervosa" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anorexia_nervosa" target="_blank">anorexia</a> she went on to develop <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bulimia_nervosa" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bulimia_nervosa" target="_blank">bulimia</a> and alcoholismThe 23yearold â who says she is now 99 per cent recovered â is sharing the ordeal she went through to try to encourage other <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Suffering" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Suffering" target="_blank">sufferers</a> to seek helpLydia said âIt was a horrible experience and I want to help others who may be <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Feeling" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Feeling" target="_blank">feeling</a> the same wayâThere were <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Times" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Times" target="_blank">times</a> when I <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thought" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thought" target="_blank">thought</a> I was going to die but I didn't know what to do â I couldn't ignore the voices telling me not to <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eating" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eating" target="_blank">eat</a>âI wanted to explain my deepest <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thought" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thought" target="_blank">thoughts</a> and how I overcame themâ<a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eating_disorder" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eating_disorder" target="_blank">Eating disorders</a> are so common now yet so few people <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Understanding" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Understanding" target="_blank">understand</a> themâPeople need to see what is behind the sad eyes of someone <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Suffering" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Suffering" target="_blank">suffering</a> with these <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Illness" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Illness" target="_blank">illnesses</a> rather than seeing only <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bone" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bone" target="_blank">bones</a>âLydia who lives in <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow" target="_blank">Glasgow</a> says her descent into <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anorexia_nervosa" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anorexia_nervosa" target="_blank">anorexia</a> started in her first year at university in 2010 after a onenight stand left her with a <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sexually_transmitted_disease" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sexually_transmitted_disease" target="_blank">sexually transmitted</a> infectionShe said âI felt so selfconscious and disgusted in myself It was only my second time with someone but afterwards I hated my bodyâI started trying to <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eating" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eating" target="_blank">eat</a> really <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Health" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Health" target="_blank">healthily</a> to counteract how I was <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Feeling" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Feeling" target="_blank">feeling</a>âLiving in a student <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gregory_House" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gregory_House" target="_blank">house</a> didn't help as I started to <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Feeling" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Feeling" target="_blank">feel</a> awkward <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eating" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eating" target="_blank">eating</a> in front of other people When I went home <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mother" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mother" target="_blank">mum</a> pointed out that I was <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eating" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eating" target="_blank">eating</a> less but I didn't give it much <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thought" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thought" target="_blank">thought</a>âAt the end of first year someone called me skinny and it stuck in my headâIt made me <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Feeling" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Feeling" target="_blank">feel</a> good about myself I went on a girls' holiday to Zante and lived off Diet CokeâMy friends noticed but I don't think they knew what to doâ Living away from home while she studied <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fashion" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fashion" target="_blank">fashion</a> in <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Newcastle_upon_Tyne" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Newcastle_upon_Tyne" target="_blank">Newcastle</a> her <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eating_disorder" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eating_disorder" target="_blank">eating disorder</a> developed to the point where she would only have three teaspoons of asparagus or spinach a dayHer intake of 13 <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Calorie" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Calorie" target="_blank">calories</a> a day â equivalent to a quarter of a jaffa cake or two walnuts â saw her drop to 4st 11lb and a size six in clothesLydia added âAt weekends I would <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eating" title="htt